body_text.text:
We have chosen our dataset from Viral siRNA database (VIRsiRNAdb) which contains over 1358 siRNA sequences targeting different human viruses and HIV siRNA database (HIVsirDB) having over 750 entries. From these databases we selected 927 and 240 sequences of 19mer which were having numerical (quantitative) efficacy. In addition 1204 sequences from patents were also used. In addition 67 more siRNAs were collected from the literature. This combined dataset of 2294 siRNAs was reduced to 1725 sequences after removal of redundant sequences. From this dataset we randomly selected 345 sequences for validation (V
345
) and the rest 1380 sequences were used in training (T
1380
).
